itunes.summary: On this episode, I am joined by Angelie, Congolese native and host of, ‘Safe, Just Another Podcast’. We begin with some background information about what is happening and been happening in the DRC ( Democratic Republic of Congo). From modern day slavery, exploitation of the people and robbing of resources, just to name a few. We then shift into the reasons that Africa remains so vulnerable to exploitation. Ranging from the children workers, little to nothing wages, raping women, lack of safety and the inability to be able to reap the benefits of their own natural resources; the steady pour into the colonizers pocket since the colonizers landed on the Continent. A country that could be so rich, remains so poor so to the robbing, exploiting and flat out modern day slavery can continue to thrive. Madness! It makes me want to throw this iPhone out! Link to research more: https://assets.publishing.service.gov.uk/media/5b9a541be5274a138ea54232/052_Modern_slavery_in_the_DRC.pdf.
